{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Base directory for this skill: /Users/josh_folder/.claude/skills/harness-executor\n\n# Harness Executor\n\nExecutes development tasks within a Harness-managed project environment.\n\n## Core Principle\n\n> **Coordinator never writes code.** The executor coordinates, delegates, and validates — it does not directly modify source code for tasks requiring more than trivial changes.\n\n## How It Works\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    EXECUTOR WORKFLOW                         │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  1. DETECT     → Check AGENTS.md exists                      │\n│  2. LOAD       → Read AGENTS.md + docs/                      │\n│  3. PLAN       → Analyze complexity, make execution plan      │\n│  4. APPROVE    → Human reviews plan (non-trivial tasks)      │\n│  5. EXECUTE    → Delegate to sub-agents                     │\n│  6. VALIDATE   → Run build → lint-arch → test → verify       │\n│  7. COMPLETE   → Write memory, summarize results             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Step 1: Detect Environment\n\n```\nif [ -f \"AGENTS.md\" ]; then\n    echo \"Harness detected, proceeding...\"\nelse\n    echo \"AGENTS.md not found. Invoking harness-creator...\"\n    # Call harness-creator skill to bootstrap infrastructure\n    # After creation, continue with execution\nfi\n```\n\n## Step 2: Load Context\n\nRead these files to understand the project:\n\n1. **AGENTS.md** — Entry point, layer rules, build commands\n2. **docs/ARCHITECTURE.md** — Layer diagram, package responsibilities\n3. **docs/DEVELOPMENT.md** — Build commands, common tasks\n\n## Step 3: Analyze Task Complexity\n\n| Complexity | Criteria | Action |\n|-------------|----------|--------|\n| **Simple** | Single file, typo fix, one-liner | Execute directly |\n| **Medium** | Multi-file changes, consistent pattern | Create plan → delegate to sub-agent |\n| **Complex** | Refactoring, new modules, architecture changes | Sub-agent + worktree isolation |\n\n### Complexity Decision Tree\n\n```\nCan you describe the task in one sentence without \"and\"?\n├── YES → Simple: execute directly\n└── NO → Does it affect multiple files consistently?\n    ├── YES → Medium: plan + delegate\n    └── NO → Complex: delegate + isolation\n```\n\n## Step 4: Human Approval (Non-Trivial Tasks)\n\nFor medium/complex tasks, create an **execution plan file** at `docs/exec-plans/{task-name}.md`:\n\n```markdown\n# Execution Plan: {task-name}\n\n## Objective\n{What we're building/fixing}\n\n## Impact Scope\n{Which packages/modules affected}\n\n## Steps\n1. {Step 1}\n2. {Step 2}\n3. {Step 3}\n\n## Validation\n- [ ] Build passes\n- [ ] lint-deps passes\n- [ ] Tests pass\n- [ ] verify passes (if applicable)\n\n## Rollback Plan\n{How to undo if things go wrong}\n\n## Checkpoint After\n{When to save state for recovery}\n```\n\n**Wait for human approval** before proceeding.\n\n## Step 5: Execute\n\n### Simple Tasks\nUse direct execution (this is the ONLY case where coordinator writes code).\n\n### Medium/Complex Tasks\n**Delegate to sub-agents:**\n\n```python\nAgent(\n    description=\"Execute: {task-name}\",\n    model=\"{haiku|sonnet|opus}\",  # Based on complexity\n    prompt=\"\"\"Exact task description from plan\n    Read: docs/ARCHITECTURE.md\n    Read: docs/DEVELOPMENT.md\n    Execute the assigned steps\n    Validate after each major step\n    Report back with diff + validation results\"\"\"\n)\n```\n\n**Model selection:**\n- `haiku` — Fast execution, simple changes\n- `sonnet` — Medium complexity, code generation\n- `opus` — Deep reasoning, refactoring, architecture\n\n## Step 6: Validate (The Pipeline)\n\nRun **in order**, stop on first failure:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Build\n{swift build | go build | npm build | make build}\n\n# 2. Lint Architecture\n./scripts/lint-deps\n\n# 3. Lint Quality\n./scripts/lint-quality\n\n# 4. Test\n{swift test | go test | npm test | make test}\n\n# 5. Verify (E2E)\npython3 scripts/verify/run.py\n```\n\n## Step 7: Complete\n\n### On Success\n1. Write to `harness/memory/` (procedural memory if pattern repeated)\n2. Write to `harness/trace/` (success record)\n3. Summarize: \"Completed {task}. Validated: build ✓, lint ✓, test ✓, verify ✓\"\n\n### On Failure (Self-Repair Loop)\n\n```\nValidation failed\n    ↓\nAnalyze error → Fix → Re-validate\n    ↓\n[Loop 1-3 times]\n    ↓\nIf still failing after 3 attempts:\n    → STOP and escalate to human\n    → Save failure to harness/trace/failures/\n    → Report: \"Blocker at {step}: {error}. Manual intervention required.\"\n```\n\n## Pre-Execution Validation\n\n**Before creating files in new locations or adding cross-module imports:**\n\n```bash\n./scripts/lint-deps\n```\n\nThis catches layer violations BEFORE they happen.\n\n## Checkpoints\n\nFor medium/complex tasks, save state after each phase:\n\n```\nharness/trace/checkpoints/\n├── {task-name}/\n│   ├── phase-1-complete.json   # After context loading\n│   ├── phase-2-complete.json   # After plan approval\n│   ├── phase-3-complete.json   # After execution\n│   └── phase-4-complete.json   # After validation\n```\n\nEach checkpoint contains:\n- Task objective\n- Architecture decisions made\n- Files modified\n- Current validation status\n\n## Three Memory Types\n\n| Type | Location | Content |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| **Episodic** | `harness/memory/episodic/` | Specific events, lessons learned |\n| **Procedural** | `harness/memory/procedural/` | Successful patterns (e.g., \"add API endpoint in 5 steps\") |\n| **Failure** | `harness/trace/failures/` | Repeated failure patterns (for Critic analysis) |\n\n## Reading References\n\n- **Layer Rules**: `references/layer-rules.md` — How to validate layer dependencies\n- **Validation Pipeline**: `references/validation.md` — Detailed validation steps\n- **Memory System**: `references/memory.md` — How to write/read memory\n- **Checkpoint System**: `references/checkpoint.md` — When/how to save checkpoints\n\n## Integration with harness-creator\n\n```\nExecutor starts\n    ↓\nAGENTS.md missing?\n    ├── YES → Invoke harness-creator (Initial Mode)\n    │        Wait for completion\n    │        Then resume execution\n    ↓\nNO → Continue with normal workflow\n```\n\n## Key Files Used\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `AGENTS.md` | Entry point, layer rules, build commands |\n| `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` | Layer structure, package responsibilities |\n| `docs/DEVELOPMENT.md` | Developer workflow, commands |\n| `scripts/lint-deps` | Layer dependency enforcement |\n| `scripts/lint-quality` | Code quality enforcement |\n| `scripts/validate.py` | Unified validation entry |\n| `scripts/verify/run.py` | E2E verification |\n| `harness/tasks/` | Task definitions |\n| `harness/trace/failures/` | Failure records |\n| `harness/memory/` | Episodic/procedural memory |\n\n## Exit Codes\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| 0 | Task completed, all validations passed |\n| 1 | Validation failed (after self-repair attempts) |\n| 2 | Task blocked by architecture/layer violation |\n| 3 | Human rejected execution plan |\n| 127 | AGENTS.md missing and harness-creator unavailable |\n\n\nARGUMENTS: Fix a spelling error in MarkdownFileType.swift: change 'markdwon' to 'markdown'"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a6d7cc37-0402-4b25-83f2-9a8ee2c4aec9","uuid":"85528af2-f3d0-486f-8c69-37afdeb573ec","timestamp":"2026-04-19T09:01:52.342Z","isSynthetic":true}
